<article>
    <h1>NEW YORK AF&#xAD;TER&#xAD;NOON TEA</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200814/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-14"><time>2020-08-14</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline">Eu&#xAD;nice Quek Food Cor&#xAD;re&#xAD;spon&#xAD;dent rec&#xAD;om&#xAD;mends</span>
    </section>

    <p>A new lux­u­ri­ous af­ter­noon tea ex­pe­ri­ence (right) at the Raf­fles Ho­tel Sin­ga­pore takes in­spi­ra­tion from the Big Ap­ple.</p>
    <p>Start with the savoury items – lob­ster roll, smoked salmon bagel and Reuben sand­wich – all filled with a gen­er­ous amount of in­gre­di­ents.</p>
    <p>Sweet treats in­clude red vel­vet cake, car­rot cake and New York cheese­cake by ex­ec­u­tive pas­try chef Tai Chien Lin.</p>
    <p>Com­plete the in­dul­gence with cock­tails ($20 each) such as Man­hat­tan, Cos­mopoli­tan and Bronx, or go for cham­pagne (from $25).</p>
    <p>The New York af­ter­noon tea ($78++ a per­son) is avail­able for a limited pe­riod, after which the city theme will change. Till Sept 30, it is part of the “3+1” group din­ing of­fer (dine in a group of four for the price of three) at the ho­tel’s Grand Lobby.</p>
    <p>WHERE: The Grand Lobby, Raf­fles Ho­tel Sin­ga­pore, 1 Beach Road</p>
    <p>MRT: City Hall WHEN: 1 to 5pm (week­days), noon to 6pm</p>
    <p>(week­ends) TEL: 6412-1816</p>
    <p>INFO: www.raf­f­lessin­ga­pore.com/res­tau­rant/the-grand-lobby</p>


